          "id": 5,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"213551\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>The running time of an algorithm is given by:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\( T(n) =&nbsp;T(n-1) +&nbsp;T(n-2) -&nbsp;T(n-3) \\), if \\( n &gt;&nbsp;3 \\)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = \\( n \\), otherwise</p>\n\n<p>Then what should be the relation between \\( T(1),&nbsp;T(2),&nbsp;T(3) \\), so that the order of the algorithm is constant?</p>\n\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\">\n\t<li>\\( T(1) =&nbsp;T(2) =&nbsp;T(3) \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( T(1) +&nbsp;T(3) = 2T(2) \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( T(1) -&nbsp;T(3) = T(2) \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( T(1) +&nbsp;T(2) = T(3) \\)</li>\n</ol></div><br><br><b>Algorithms: ISRO CSE 2018 | Question: 37</b></p>",
